<paragraph blockId="19.[714,1247,1364,1667]" pageId="19" pageNumber="78">
Plants to 
<quantity box="[853,925,1364,1391]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="78" unit="cm" value="20.0">20 cm</quantity>
high, stem subterranean or reaching 
<quantity box="[828,903,1394,1421]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="78" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
above ground; corm with a crescent-shaped basal ridge. Leaves 3-5, the lower 2-3 basal, filiform, narrowly 4-grooved, straight or curved; outer bracts with narrow membranous margins, inner bracts with wide transparent or brown-flecked margins. Flowers pink to coppery salmon, rarely white, unscented, tepals elliptic, 
<quantity box="[714,838,1609,1636]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="19" pageNumber="78" unit="mm" value="28.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="16.0">16-40 mm</quantity>
long; filaments inserted above the middle of the tube, 
<quantity box="[946,1053,1640,1667]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="78" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="4.0">4-10 mm</quantity>
long, often dark
</paragraph>
